        <h2>Pricing breakdown</h2>
        <p>Buildertrend uses flat-rate monthly pricing regardless of team size — unlimited users across all plans. This is a genuine advantage for larger teams:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Essential: $499/mo — core PM, scheduling, client portal, daily logs</li>
          <li>Advanced: $799/mo — advanced reporting, integrations</li>
          <li>Complete: $1,099/mo — lead management, bidding, full financial suite</li>
        </ul>

        <p>UDA ConstructionOnline pricing varies based on company size and selected features. Entry packages start around $200–400/month for smaller companies. Contact UDA for current pricing as published rates change frequently.</p>

        <p><strong>Bottom line on pricing:</strong> ConstructionOnline is typically less expensive, but Buildertrend's unlimited user model means large teams can end up with a better cost-per-user at Buildertrend's flat rate.</p>

        <h2>Estimating: ConstructionOnline wins</h2>
        <p>UDA's estimating module is the platform's strongest differentiator. It includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pre-built cost library with thousands of line items organized by CSI division</li>
          <li>Assembly-based estimating for repetitive components</li>
          <li>Integration with RSMeans cost data</li>
          <li>Polished proposal generation directly from estimate data</li>
          <li>Specification writing tools integrated with estimates</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Buildertrend's estimating is competent but less deep. For contractors who live in their estimate — custom homebuilders producing detailed line-item bids, design-build firms creating specifications — ConstructionOnline has a meaningful advantage.</p>

        <h2>Client experience: Buildertrend wins</h2>
        <p>Buildertrend's client portal is one of the most praised features in all of construction software. Homeowners log in to see their project schedule, approve selections, review change orders, sign digitally, view progress photos, and make payments — all in a clean, mobile-friendly interface.</p>

        <p>ConstructionOnline has a client portal, but Buildertrend's is more polished, more feature-complete, and better designed for the emotionally involved homeowner who wants constant visibility into their project.</p>

        <h2>Scheduling: Buildertrend wins</h2>
        <p>Buildertrend's Gantt scheduling is visual, intuitive, and handles dependencies with automatic cascade updates when tasks shift. For builders managing complex multi-trade schedules across concurrent projects, it's excellent.</p>

        <p>ConstructionOnline's scheduling is functional but less visually refined. It handles the basics and supports schedule templates, but it won't impress the way Buildertrend's scheduling view does.</p>

        <h2>Mobile experience: Buildertrend wins</h2>
        <p>Buildertrend's mobile app is among the best in the industry — crew members can log daily reports, submit photos, track time, and view schedules from the field. ConstructionOnline has a mobile app, but it's less capable and less frequently praised by users.</p>

        <h2>Specifications: ConstructionOnline wins</h2>
        <p>For contractors who produce detailed project specifications as part of their contracts — particularly design-build firms and custom homebuilders working in markets where spec-writing is expected — ConstructionOnline's spec tools are a significant advantage that Buildertrend simply doesn't match.</p>

        <h2>When to choose Buildertrend</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You're a residential GC or remodeler and want the market-leading platform</li>
          <li>Client experience and portal quality matter to your business</li>
          <li>You have a larger team (10+ users) where flat-rate pricing is advantageous</li>
          <li>Mobile field use is important — daily logs, photos, time tracking from job sites</li>
          <li>You want the most integrations and the largest support ecosystem</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>Buildertrend is the market standard for residential construction management.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.buildertrend.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn">Try Buildertrend</a>
        </div>

        <h2>When to choose Construction Online</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Estimating depth and specification writing are core to your workflow</li>
          <li>You're a smaller company where lower pricing is a priority</li>
          <li>You prefer a Windows desktop application alongside cloud access</li>
          <li>Your clients are less hands-on and a premium client portal matters less</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The verdict</h2>
        <p>Buildertrend wins for most residential contractors. Its client portal, scheduling, mobile experience, and market dominance make it the safer and generally stronger choice. ConstructionOnline is the right pick for contractors who live in their estimates and produce detailed specs — and who find Buildertrend's pricing harder to justify at their current revenue level.</p>

